250 grams Irish Beef Mince
1 pack(s) Chopped Tomato with Onion & Garlic
3 unit(s) Potatoes
60 grams Baby Spinach
125 grams Mozzarella
1 pack(s) Breadcrumbs
1 sachet(s) Mustard
1 sachet(s) Worcester Sauce
to taste Oil
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
to taste Sugar
to taste Butter

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).
Pop the potatoes onto a large (lined) baking tray.
Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer (leaving room for the meatballs).

To a large bowl, add the beef mince, breadcrumbs, mustard and Worcester sauce.
Season with salt and pepper then mix everything together with your hands.
Once combined, form into evenly-sized meatballs, 5 per person. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat.
When the oven is hot, cook the potatoes and beef meatballs together for 15 mins.
TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Meanwhile, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Add the chopped tomato, 1 tsp sugar and 50ml water (double both for 4p). Simmer until slightly thickened, 5-7 mins.
Stir in the spinach and cook until warmed through, 1-2 mins.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Stir through a knob of butter.

When the potatoes and meatballs have been cooking for 15 mins, remove the meatballs from the oven (leaving the potatoes to cook).
Add the meatballs to an oven dish.
Stir in the simmered spinach sauce.
Drain then roughly tear the mozzarella and spread it on top.

Place the oven dish in the oven below the potatoes.
Bake everything until the mozzarella has melted and the potatoes are tender, 10-15 mins. IMPORTANT: Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Divide the mozzarella meatballs between plates.
Serve with the crispy potatoes alongside.